I remember one from my teen years. What I remember from the dream was flying up to the edge of space, but earth had misty clouds that blended with it's blue light, and was filled with "snowflakes" and slow moving baby blue geometric shapes (primarily hexagons) like a trippier PlayStation 4 home screen. I remember feeling weightless and elated, but something was floating to me. It looked feral, but regal at the same time. The best way I could describe it at this moment is that it was a combination of a wendigo and Krystal. It's face was a blur, but there was blueish jewelry and a dress that was sky blue and dark blue that reminded me of how seaweed moves. Then I just slowly fell and saw all white.
I don't have dreams often, so the ones I have tend to stick with me. This was by far the weirdest.
